## 2026-06-02: StreamClient — Bidirectional Streaming gRPC Client

### Files Created
# opensearch_grpc/stream_client.py — Persistent streaming client
#   - Maintains a persistent gRPC channel (no reconnection per request)
#   - Client streams operations continuously: .index(), .create(), .update(), .delete()
#   - .flush() sends all queued ops as one BulkRequest, returns responses
#   - Auto-flush mode: set batch_size=N to auto-send every N operations
#   - Context manager: with StreamClient() as client: ...
#   - On close: flushes remaining ops and closes channel
#
# How bidirectional works:
#   - Current proto: DocumentService.Bulk is unary (BulkRequest → BulkResponse)
#   - We simulate bidirectional by: persistent channel + batched flushes
#   - Client keeps queueing operations → flush sends batch → server responds
#   - Multiple flushes on same channel = continuous streaming without reconnection
#   - When proto adds true stream RPC, internal changes but API stays same
#
# References used:
#   - https://grpc.io/docs/languages/python/basics/ (gRPC streaming patterns)
#   - https://docs.opensearch.org/latest/api-reference/grpc-apis/bulk/ (Bulk gRPC API)
#   - https://docs.opensearch.org/latest/api-reference/grpc-apis/index/ (gRPC overview)
